FortyTwo BBS Upgrade Status
===========================

FortyTwo BBS is currently pre-alpha software.

There is no supported upgrade procedure between development versions and no
supported migration path from an existing MBSE BBS installation.

Development versions may change:

- configuration files
- directory structures
- database and binary file formats
- user and permission models
- service definitions
- internal program interfaces

Do not install a newer development version over an existing installation.

Use a separate, isolated test environment for each development version and
keep independent backups of all data and configuration files.

The inherited MBSE BBS ChangeLog contains historical upgrade instructions.
Those instructions apply only to the corresponding historical MBSE BBS
versions and must not be treated as FortyTwo BBS upgrade instructions.

A documented and tested upgrade procedure will be introduced before a
production-ready FortyTwo BBS release.

Current tested development platform:

- Ubuntu 25.10
- x86_64
- glibc-based Linux

